The second season of Hataraku Maou-sama! MgRonalds best demon lord worker is back, climbing the corporate ladder to become ruler of Earth. But Maous plans of domination might need to be put on hold when a small girl claims to be his and Emis child! (Source: Crunchyroll)

A strange turn of events leads the Dragon, Tohru, to work as Miss Kobayashi's maid. She occasionally (that's a lie, she often) causes trouble for her beloved Miss Kobayashi while blending into human society and splendidly (that's a lie, only mediocrely) carrying out her maid duties. Her fellow dragons, Kanna, Lucoa, Fafnir, and Elma all find their own places to fit in as well and enjoy interspecies interactions with the humans. Yet while they're all enjoying that laid-back and occasionally turbulent left, the threat of a new Dragon swoops down upon Miss Kobayashi.
(Source: Crunchyroll)
(Kono Sekai wa Mou Ore ga Sukutte Tomi to Kenryoku wo Te ni Iretashi, Onna Kishi ya Onna Maou to Shiro de Tanoshiku Kurashiteru kara, Ore Igai no Yuusha wa) Mou Isekai ni Konaide Kudasai.

[Question] A new different world hero appeared on Horizon [Answer] Turn back to Earth right now!
After the struggle, I saved the other world and tried to enjoy the rest of my life freely. But for some reason, the incarnating hero from the earth will spring up here on the Horizon. Don't be silly! This world is mine!
The Holy Knight, the Demon Girl, the Elves, the Beastmen, and even the ordinary people, everything in this world will never be given to anyone!
NEET? Izakaya? SDF? No matter who the enemy is! Other-hero, turn back to the Earth!
Drive back all the other world hero with wisdom, courage and perfection, a slapstick fantasy opens!
(Source: Kadokawa, translated)

The story is about Ine and Shouzou, two pensioners well into their 80s who are mysteriously returned to their 20s one night. Note: Sixth place of Tsugimanga 2020 Award in the Web Manga Category Jiisan Baasan Wakagaeru is a web manga released on the author's pixiv and Twitter accounts, and later picked for print release by Kadokawa. Includes 4 extra chapters
